<Class name="WS_FieldDefinition" id="9bb58a43-6d7b-4fe8-8214-4a23dc5c9373">
    <superclass name="WS_Form_Object"/>
    <transient/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>This class is designed for the JMT RIA.</text>
    <DbClassMap file="webservice"/>
    <PrimAttribute name="controlType" id="e4d81560-fc9c-48ac-b36a-0de555f9cbef">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>Defines the type of control as follows:

0	-	Text Box
1	-	MultiLine Text Box
2	-	Combo Box
3	-	List Box
4	-	Check Box
5	-	Date Field
6	-	Numeric Field
9	-	Group Header
10	-	Checkable Group Header
101	-	Time Picker - application specific
102	-	Recepient Picker - application specific</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="dataList" id="4ddd4a67-ce93-4ca4-9187-9076f70faac5">
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>Instead of providing a webservice name to call via dataStore,
the webservice can provide the list of data inline. This would typically 
be used for only very short, fixed stores such as a "yes, no, maybe, n/a" 
combo or somesuch. The dataList parameter would contain an array of values
similar to the list given above for dataStore, and would allow the 
repeatedStoreField, storeDescriptionField, and storeIdField parameters 
to be specified like dataStore.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="dataReloadField" id="8ed24bcf-694d-41e1-9a0e-a9a4d9993714">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>The key value of another field. 
When the value of that field changes, the data cache associated 
with this field is refreshed from the webserver
</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="dataStore" id="98f56058-99ca-41a6-88fb-c950dee9d50b">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>Combo boxes and listboxes need data to populate them. The data store specifies
the name of the web service where appropriate data can be obtained. The 
webservice will be sent a message with no parameters. That webservice 
may return a message similar to the following:

&lt;items&gt;
	&lt;item&gt;
		&lt;id&gt;1&lt;/id&gt;
		&lt;display&gt;"Henry's Dairy"&lt;/display&gt;
	&lt;/item&gt;
	&lt;item&gt;
		&lt;id&gt;27&lt;/id&gt;
		&lt;display&gt;"Bob's Takeaways"&lt;/display&gt;
	&lt;/item&gt;
&lt;/items&gt;

</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="defaultDescription" id="ba4a3410-48dc-4623-9575-5cbb91f8d965">
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>A value to display for the field by default when a new record is being created

    
</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="defaultId" id="1bb7e67d-9c57-4ca5-8f3d-e5e90bfcd055">
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>An internal value to associate with the field by default when a new record
 is being created. Eg if the defaultDescription is "ISO Container" the defaultId would be 1.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="descAbbreviation" id="d4cc1a77-7601-4537-a06a-c6fc6bf23d40">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="initialFieldForSaveNext" id="0ace31bd-dff1-4924-82d7-8b968c6b2037">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="isHiddenInThumbnail" id="04ba02cc-a745-44e7-8b95-1eadd1cbe163">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="isMandatory" id="2f9ed724-c743-4a00-b71d-3e507e0390c4">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="isUppercaseText" id="f48bfbc5-6527-460e-b8c3-6a7b4d0590ed">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="key" id="87d76bc9-0e99-4483-a628-cd1d7c435686">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>Name of the control</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="label" id="cab6c541-f117-4786-8455-ee77701bd190">
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>the label text that will be displayed beside the form field, 
or the heading that will be displayed for control type 9.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="layoutDriverName" id="3f93a1ab-7602-4b35-a2d7-a9336f808e64">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="maxTextLength" id="d04bdfec-b6f9-4182-a04e-32d5e53c2e4d">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <ExplicitInverseRef name="myFormDefinition" id="1de047ae-0ac4-489f-9c0b-f9792b304c2e">
        <kind>child</kind>
        <updateMode>manual</updateMode>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="WS_FormDefinition"/>
        <Inverse name="WS_FormDefinition::allFormFields"/>
        <Inverse name="WS_FormDefinition::allFormFieldsByKey"/>
    </ExplicitInverseRef>
    <PrimAttribute name="parent" id="fd7e5cc1-3bf8-4f05-bc3b-2611c268bee3">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>the key value of the parent control - when left empty it defaults to form 
(ie doesn't get put in a drop-down category)</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="readOnly" id="c95372a4-3cd0-4514-a1ec-89d01b7b1bb5">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <text>True if the field cannot be modified
</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="readOnlyAlways" id="5b48fd72-ab99-410a-9e11-e217184c441c">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="repeatedStoreField" id="0a24f7af-dd45-4587-8e91-05dcf2433afb">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>The name of the repeating field in the XML (ie the Jade class name of the type in the array)</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="showTableColumn" id="37368106-f0e0-43e2-9306-1f59c812f8a5">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <text>Specifies whether and how the table of search results will include this field as a column

      : 0 Visible (default) - this column is visible

      : 1 Invisible - the column is invisible but available for the user to make visible

      : 2 Unavailable - the user can never see this column (default for controlType 9)

</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="storeDescriptionField" id="587d02d7-0d76-4ef1-987d-cac88c5c142c">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>The name of the attribute containing the values that the user gets to choose from
(in this case 'display'). If this is not specified, the client will assume that 
the array being returned is a primitive array and that the values within it are 
the primitive strings (eg &lt;item&gt;One&lt;/item&gt; &lt;item&gt;Two&lt;/item&gt;)</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="storeIdField" id="bb07f5e1-4c94-4692-9117-430ca62b00cd">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>The name of the attribute containing the hidden Id values associated with the displayed data.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="useRealObject" id="98245ba4-0afb-4e8c-a74e-57e234b78591">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="visibilityToggleField" id="608466c4-64ec-4958-9c61-10ae81814694">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>The key value of another field. The current field is hidden unless that field
has a non-false value.

</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <JadeMethod name="isVisibleInTable" id="056079b8-2b35-4a10-8ad6-869c9cc08ba9">
        <source>isVisibleInTable() : Boolean;

/*

Purpose:			

Parameters:			

Return Value:		


Date		Who		Reason
06 October 2008	cnwkao1	Initial creation

*/
begin
	return	self.showTableColumn = WS_FormDefinition.Visibility_OnlyInTableInvis or
			self.showTableColumn = WS_FormDefinition.Visibility_Visible;
	
end;</source>
        <ReturnType type="Boolean"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="setDefaultsForReports" id="bbf8ec32-d8d7-4955-bfa0-e2711f2e66d1">
        <updating/>
        <source>setDefaultsForReports() updating;
/*

Purpose:			

Parameters:			

Return Value:		

Date		Who		Reason
08 Mar 2018	jlger1	Initial creation 37479
17 Feb 2020 cnwma1	Bug 48590: ADP - Passing Invoice Status is not Working when passed by web services
*/

vars
	date 		  : Date;
	defaultObject : Object;
	invalidObj 	  : Boolean;
	ed 			  : Integer;
begin
	if self.defaultDescription = Any_String then   //9/10/2009 cnwdz2 21129
		if self.key &lt;&gt; "invoiceStatus" then        // 17.02.2020 cnwma1 #48590
			self.defaultDescription := null;
		endif;
	endif;
			
	if self.controlType = WS_FormDefinition.ControlType_CheckBox then
		//cnwmc5 - PAR 32206 - 5 Sep 2013
		self.defaultDescription := self.defaultDescription.asBooleanJMT().String;//app.getYesNo(fieldDef.defaultDescription.asBooleanJMT());
	endif;
			
	///19/07/2010 cnwdz2 24513
	if self.defaultId = null then
		self.defaultId := self.defaultDescription;		
	endif;
			
	if self.controlType = WS_FormDefinition.ControlType_DateField then	//12 Dec 2017	NDL	TFS 8090 i.e is configured as a date field for input
		//cnwmc5 - 20 June 2014 - PAR 34398
		date := self.defaultId.asDateJMT();
		if date.isValid then
			self.defaultId := date.asStringForWebInterface();
			self.defaultDescription := date.asStringForWebInterface();
		endif;
	endif;
	
	if self.controlType = WS_FormDefinition.ControlType_ComboBox or
				self.controlType = WS_FormDefinition.ControlType_ListBox or
				self.controlType = WS_FormDefinition.ControlType_MultiTextBox then
		//chances are that it will be a real object - so use the OID and handle the special cases 
		//if self.dataStore &lt;&gt; JMTUserInterfaceService::getCargoTypes.name then
			self.storeIdField := WS_ProxyObject::cmObjectId.name;
		//endif;
	endif;
	
	//don't show default id if invalid or for wrong terminal
	if self.defaultId &lt;&gt; null then
		defaultObject:=self.defaultId.asOid;
		
		if defaultObject &lt;&gt; null then
			on Exception do app.handleDeletedObject(exception,defaultObject,invalidObj);
			ed := defaultObject.edition;
			if invalidObj then
				defaultObject:=null;
			else 
				if defaultObject.getMyTerminal &lt;&gt; null and defaultObject.getMyTerminal  &lt;&gt; app.myPassport.myTerminal then
					defaultObject:=null;
				endif;
			endif;
			if defaultObject = null then
				self.defaultId:=null;
				self.defaultDescription:=null;
			endif;		
		endif;
	endif;
epilog

end;</source>
    </JadeMethod>
</Class>
